entries.femaleVariant: Why the hell... not?
Don't love it, no. Got no idea who might suddenly walk in while we're fast asleep...
entries.maleVariant: Don't love it, no. Got no idea who this belongs to, what we'll find inside, who might suddenly walk in...

entries.femaleVariant: Well... all right, then.
No dice. Let's go.
Well... all right, then. You're the boss.
Don't need to be so tactical with everything, y'know. You're not on the clock here.
Our charming lakeside cottage awaits.
Eh... I don't think so, Judy. It was nice hangin' with you, but... the city beckons.
entries.maleVariant: I don't think so, Judy. It was nice hangin' with ya, but... the city beckons.

entries.femaleVariant: OK... I understand.
What an incredible dive. Doesn't get more relaxing than that.
entries.maleVariant: What an incredible dive. Doesn't get more relaxin' than that.

entries.femaleVariant: All those people from the town... It's depressing.
Most nomads have a story like that. And all of 'em begin with the same thing – displacement.
Think you could've fine-tuned the emotive wave transmitters better back there.
Got some serious surges from you a few times.
entries.maleVariant: Feed I was pickin' up felt a bit... flat – I wanna say?

entries.femaleVariant: Stay... where, exactly? We gonna camp on the shore?
Nope. There. Our cottage for the day.
entries.maleVariant: No. In there. Crash there sometimes after dives.

entries.femaleVariant: How 'bout it?
Been comin' here years and nothing's happened. C'mon, live a little! Don't make me beg.
Attagirl. Was startin' to suspect you might be a bore.
entries.maleVariant: Attaboy! Was startin' to suspect you might be a bore.

entries.femaleVariant: Shit...
Something the matter?
entries.maleVariant: Somethin' the matter?

entries.femaleVariant: [Touch] It is ours.
[Lean away] Bad idea.
It is ours.
Not a great idea, I don't think.
Sorry... I-I'm just tired. D-don't know what I'm doin'...
Grr, this chick gets on my nerves. Let's you and me blow.
[Lie down]
Comin' with?
entries.maleVariant: Ya comin' with?

entries.femaleVariant: No, I'll, um... stay out here a little.
No… Nothing.
What was that? Couldn't hear you clearly.
Hey, Judy. About that coffee...
Judy...?
[Sit] We're still synced.
[Sit] Thinkin' about Evelyn?
[Sit] Don't trust me?
Clouds has... gone to shit. Tyger Claw nonecks took revenge for Hiromi and the rest. There was a firefight.
Tom's dead. Roxanne barely got out alive... House's closed until further notice.
Rather not talk or think about it...
Maiko's holdin' all of Clouds at gunpoint. Decides every little thing, apparently...
But...?
No but. Talked to the dolls – they don't see any change. Everything's just like it was before.
I didn't wanna tell you... Wanted this to be just our day...
Don't bullshit me, Judy. We're still synced, remember?
You thinkin' about Evelyn?
Still don't trust me...? After all we've been through?
entries.maleVariant: Still don't trust me? After all we been through?

entries.femaleVariant: Got a feelin' everything we did was wasted effort.
Didn't wanna tell you... Didn't want you to think I blame you in any way.
[Comfort] Why didn't you wanna tell me?
Why didn't you say anything earlier? I don't get it.
What good would that've done? You'd just think I was blamin' you...
Blame myself already. That's enough.
[Kiss] Stop thinking about it.
You'd blame yourself even more if you hadn't tried.
Things could still work out.
Look at it this way – things couldn't get any worse, right? Which means things're only lookin' up from here.
You were just out to help the dolls. Bet you'd be blamin' yourself even more if you hadn't tried.
Think I'll... go lie down. I'm beat.
Not like you could stand by and do nothin', anyway. Not your style.
entries.maleVariant: It's not like you could stand by and do nothin', anyway. Not your style.

entries.femaleVariant: Maybe you're right...
Oh damn, I-- I'd love to share your optimism...
Just don't wake her up.
Why would you even assume I'd think that?
Dunno, I-- I'm sorry. Let's just kill the subject.
Not about to leave her here alone.
You fuckin' blow if you can. Not about to leave her alone, middle of nowhere.
She pisses you off? Why?
Judy pisses you off? Why, 'cause she cares about people an' that reminds you you're a narcissistic asshole?
entries.maleVariant: Judy pisses you off – why? 'Cause she cares about people? And that reminds you you're a narcissistic asshole?

entries.femaleVariant: Ugh, can't talk to you when you get this... sentimental. Waste of words. Least take a nap so we don't have to argue.
She's all over the place. Refuses to take the door, jumps out a window, then acts all surprised when she gets hurt.
She reminds you of Alt, doesn't she?
Oh, for-- No! Nobody's even close to Alt and what me and her had.
Let's get the fuck away, can we?
Don't really like the idea, do you…?
Forget it, Jude. It's Japantown.
[Knock] Did you say something?
[Knock] About that coffee...
Think I, uh, need to lie down.
...h-hear me? You need to wake up!
Oh, thank fuck! You're alive....
What happened?
What happened...?
Dunno. Didn't think about it. Just did what I had to do.
So, you're sayin'... you saved my life. Heh... Thank you.
entries.maleVariant: So, you're sayin'... you saved my life. Thank you.

entries.femaleVariant: You passed out.
Told you diving into this toxic waste was gonna end badly.
"Toxic waste"...? Is that your construct?
Heard somethin' weird just now... Sounded like... complaining?
That's Johnny Silverhand's construct.
Oh, it's nothing.
Remember the Relic? Reason for the whole damn heist...
entries.maleVariant: You remember the Relic? The reason for the whole damn heist...

entries.femaleVariant: Johnny Silverhand's digitized psyche was on it, and... well, his personality's seeping into my mind, taking over.
entries.maleVariant: Well, Johnny Silverhand's digitized psyche was on it, and well... his personality's seepin' into my mind, taking over.

entries.femaleVariant: You could say his mind's overwriting mine.
Oh shit, V... That mean you're... disappearing? Can you stop it?
Got an idea, a plan, just... don't know if it'll... well, work.
entries.maleVariant: I got an idea, a plan, but... I just don't know if it'll... well, work.

entries.femaleVariant: I been... feelin' a bit... burned out lately, that's all.
entries.maleVariant: Been feelin' a bit... burned out lately. That's all.

entries.femaleVariant: Hmph, if you say so...
Why do I even bother...?
Doubt you should go back to the city just now... I'm pretty beat too – last thing I wanna do is drive.
[Stand] Why not.
Bad idea, prolly.
After you.
Must be chilled to the bone. I'll brew a pot.
Black.
With sugar.
With milk.
With milk and sugar.
Black, please.
entries.maleVariant: Uh, black, please.

entries.femaleVariant: Two sugars, please.
Splash of milk'll do.
entries.maleVariant: A splash of milk'll do.

entries.femaleVariant: Milk and sugar, please.
Ahh... Forgot to start the generator.
Like the heart of a merc.
Mmm... tough on the outside... sweet on the inside.
Heh, same as me.
Goin' all in, huh?
[Start generator]
Power's up!
V! Please...
Hey! Careful, easy now...
How'd you manage to lift me out?
But you just don't fuckin' listen!
You... heard him?
Please just ignore his babbling. It's a... complicated relationship.
Eh, "heard's" overstating. It just... surfaced in my head... a thought that wasn't mine or completely yours.
You heard that...? Incredible. I-it never happened before, but... no worries, it's-- it's Johnny Silverhand's construct.
entries.maleVariant: You heard that...? S'incredible. Never happened before... But no worries, it's... Johnny Silverhand's construct.

entries.femaleVariant: Heard his thoughts, not mine.
entries.maleVariant: You heard his thoughts, not mine.

entries.femaleVariant: Johnny…? What?!
It just... sounded weird. As if it wasn't you.
Ignore him.
You heard him?
Nothin' to be losin' any sleep over.
Let's stay the night. Whaddaya think?
Stay... where, exactly?
How do you take yours?
I can turn it on.
I can go turn it on.
A generator? How luxurious.
You're gonna take it easy.
Promise to take it slow.
A generator? What's next – jacuzzi? Heh, Finnish sauna?
entries.maleVariant: A generator? Heh... what's next – jacuzzi? Finnish sauna?

entries.femaleVariant: No, but there is runnin' water.
Your little spa's open for business.
[Get up] How'd you pull me out?
"Complaining"? That the best you got, kid?
V?
And here we go...
Who's cottage is it?
Who's cottage is that, then? You said you knew the owner.
One of our neighbors was hell-bent on staying in Laguna Bend. Badges literally dragged him out of his house before the water came in.
Changed my mind. I'll stay.
Sure you don't wanna come back with me?
All right, changed my mind... I'll stay.
Sure you don't wanna come back to the city with me?
Just go already, OK?
Too late. Said you wanted to go – so go.
I'm sure.
Fine. Let's go.
Have it your way. Let's go.
Best decision you've made all day.
So he built himself another house as close as he possibly could, but... then he got sick. Water was way more toxic back then.
[Stand]
Remember the Relic we stole?
Nothing. Forget it.
Got a plan. Sort of.
Don't worry about it.
Sure you're all right?
Everything chill? You OK?
I-I wanted...
Speakin' of harm's way. Know what I see lookin' at you?
Walking, talking corpses.
You go that route, city'll always win. So be careful.
'Course I will be.
